Below are two targeted diffs that (1) enable Numba’s cache to avoid repeated compile overhead and (2) switch the `s=1.0` large-`n` path over to your fused energy+gradient kernel so you only do one loop instead of two.  These changes should cut both compile and runtime overhead on the 1 / riesz_energy_n20_s1 metric without touching the high-level logic.

